They get so worked up about telling the heros backstory, making a world threatening villain, etc etc.. But we've had the same movie over and over and Im so tired of that. Thats one of the reasons Im not excited to see the Black Widow movie, because it looks like hero movie #65 or something.
But this is diferent, its fun, it doesnt take itself too seriously but it also delivers a message.
Anyways, thats just my opinion :)

snippet.textDisplay:
Okay here’s what I think (warning long paragraph below) :
We all spent 2019 crying. We cried watching Avengers Endgame, we cried watching Game of thrones (even if it was bad idc we cried), then we cried watching It chapter 2, we cried watching Joker, we cried watching Star wars. These movies were obviously beautiful, deep n shit but I think Birds of Prey was exactly the refreshing movie we all needed. Like, it was fun, simple plot but enjoyable, and finally it had a really GOOD ENDING with all the characters ALIVE and HAPPY (not sionis of course lol) and Harley finally got to eat her sandwich (pretty satisfying wbk). So yeah, it wasn’t an emotional and beautiful movie with deep meanings but we enjoyed it and I think it was exactly what BoP has been created for. Thanks for coming to my ted talk, love <3

snippet.textDisplay: I strongly disagree with your points about the characters in this movie. I mean yeah, they don't spend as much time with the other characters as they do with Harley, but I didn't mind at all because I thought it was pretty obvious that this is Harley's movie from the start. But they do give us a lot of things to work with from the other characters, and I for one found myself really caring about the Birds of Prey (Montoya, Huntress, Canary) at the end of it. Their dynamic is fun and feels fresh, and I do think that they are a strong team of characters. The plot might be basic, but I think that the characters make it work. I love this take on Huntress especially. Everyone really shines in their performance and it just brings the whole movie together for me. I could not stop smiling through the whole thing, it's just so much fun with great action scenes and an amazing cast.
